# mbedTLS source vendored from upstream. include/ + LICENSE ARE committed
# (2.4 MB of headers) so devs don't have to run the vendor dance just to
# compile the engine — too many fresh clones were failing on missing
# <mbedtls/ssl.h> during Wii/GCN builds. The .c sources (library/) and the
# rest of the upstream tree are still ignored; we only need them when
# rebuilding the lib-wii/lib-gcn archives, which is a maintainer task.
library/
3rdparty/
scripts/
framework/
tf-psa-crypto/
_clone/

# The compiled archives ARE committed — devs shouldn't need to redo the
# vendor + build dance just to compile the engine. Re-run build_dolphin_docker.sh
# only when bumping mbedTLS or changing the user config.
!lib-wii/
!lib-gcn/
!lib-wii/*.a
!lib-gcn/*.a

# Container build cache, intermediate object dirs.
*.o
library-build-*/
